node.text:
This month is #SuicidePreventionMonth. Please share this as far and wide as you can to spread awareness. 

Follow @fightthroughmentalhealth for more awareness. 

Here are some suicide warning signs:
⚠️ social withdrawal
⚠️ a persistent drop in mood
⚠️ disinterest in maintaining personal hygiene or appearance
⚠️ uncharacteristically reckless behaviour
⚠️ poor diet changes
⚠️ rapid weight changes
⚠️ being distracted
⚠️ anger
⚠️ insomnia
⚠️ alcohol or drug abuse
⚠️ giving away sentimental or expensive possessions

#mentalhealthawareness #mentalillnessmatters #mentalhealth #mentalillness #suicideprevention 
#mentalhealthsupport #depression #anxiety #mentalhealthrecovery #mentalhealthadvocate

May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'jules rylan @radiantbutch here's to the people who's trauma did not give them thick skin. the ones who became more sensitive and insecure, who cry more easily, who get overwhelmed at small things. i'm so tired of the narrative that rauma makes you tough and untouchable. we're survivors, not superheroes.'.

Photo by Fight Through Mental Health on August 28, 2021. May be an image of text that says '76% of all all suicides are by men, with suicide being the biggest cause of death for men under 35. Yet, men are less likely to access psychological therapies than women. We need to break the stigma and end the silence. Do not 'Man Up', it's time to talk.'.
